wikipedia_page.main: Henri Josse (1828–23 July 1893) was a British politician. He was elected as a Liberal Member of Parliament for Great Grimsby in 1892, resigning in 1893 by becoming Steward of the Manor of Northstead. Josse was a naturalised Frenchman, he was a coal merchant in Grimsby as well as a banker in Paris.Josee resigned his seat in parliament in February 1893 due to pressure of business, he died a few months later on 23 July 1893.
